instances.excerpt: Since the 2015 adoption of the Sustainable Development Goals, adolescent birth rates declined 13% globally.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: But progress has stalled in other areas. For instance, the global maternal mortality ratio has barely changed. It remains more than 3x higher than the target set for 2030.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: In a just and equitable world, sexual and reproductive health and rights would be treated as basic health care, not a political issue, and all individuals would have the knowledge, resources, and autonomy to make informed decisions about their sexual and reproductive lives.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Our new comment in @thelancetgroup outlines the work needed to advance sexual and reproductive health and rights for everyone by 2030. We call on countries to include #SRH services in universal health plans and budgets.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Access the full article via the link in our bio

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Happy Thanks Birth Control Day!

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Its a great time to remember that contraception is a core component of reproductive autonomy and should be available to anyone who needs itincluding trans and nonbinary folks, young people and those living with low incomes.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: We know that people use birth control for many reasons, including to avoid pregnancy, have healthier pregnancies or help time and space births, and more. Thats why everyone deserves access to the full range of high-quality, affordable birth control methods that work best for them.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Were also excited for the first over-the-counter birth control pill to become available in the US early next year! This could significantly increase contraceptive access for many people.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: But our work to protect access is far from over.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: The same legal arguments used to overturn Roe also threaten the right to birth control. With the health and rights of many people at risk, we cant take anything for granted. The fight to ensure reproductive freedom for all must continue!

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: We're proud to stand with @powertodecide and @bedsider today and every day to say #ThxBirthControl!

instances.excerpt: Ohioans proved yet again that when abortion rights are on the ballot, abortion wins.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: The stakes are high for 2024. Abortion rights measures are already on 2024 ballots in New York and Maryland, and more states are aiming to do the same. Heres what you need to know:

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: The #NewYork measure would enshrine protection based on characteristics like sexual orientation, gender and pregnancy in the state constitution. It would also protect residents from government actions that would curtail repro autonomy or access to care.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: The ballot measure in #Maryland would establish a right to reproductive freedom in the state constitution. This is a powerful safeguard against future attacks if state leadership changes.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Campaigns are also underway to get an abortion rights measure on the ballot in 2024 in other states across the US.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: The overturning of Roe was a shock, but voters and policymakers are taking action at the state level to protect and expand abortion access. These fights are critical, but federal protections are also urgently needed to ensure access for all!

Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Were celebrating our 55th year of advancing sexual and reproductive health and rights!

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Since 1968, the Guttmacher Institute has envisioned a world where everyone can make decisions about their lives, bodies and futures with dignity and autonomy. Weve fought to make this a reality through innovative research, incisive policy analysis and evidence-based advocacy.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Our work has led to many historic winsfrom our input in the creation of Title X in the US, the only federal program dedicated to providing family planning services to people living with low incomes, to our role in facilitating the decriminalization of abortion in countries like Colombia and Ireland...

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: In short, weve helped to fuel the fight for reproductive health and rights for more than half a century.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Today this fight is more necessary than ever as attacks on bodily autonomy increase in post-Roe America and globally. But we arent going anywhere.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Were reenergized by a commitment to center equity, justice and the needs of marginalized communities. And were doubling down on our mission to advance #SRHR through scientific research, forward-looking analysis and equitable partnerships.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: These efforts wouldn't be possible without the generosity of our supporters.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Together with allies like you, we can double down on our mission to advance SRHR for the next 55 years and beyond.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Stay tuned to learn more about our work and join us as we continue celebrating more than half a century of impact!

instances.excerpt: It's been 47 years since the Hyde Amendment was first enacted. This US policy withholds abortion coverage from millions of people enrolled in Medicaid and other federal programs across 32 states and DC.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Most of these states also have total abortion bans or bans based on gestational duration. Hyde increases barriers to care, even for people in states where abortion remains legal.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: We also know that the harm of Hyde falls hardest on communities that have been systematically excluded from economic opportunity, including women with low incomes and people of color.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: This racist and coercive policy must end once and for all.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Congress can remove Hyde and related coverage bans by passing the Equal Access to Abortion Coverage in Health Insurance (EACH) Act, which would guarantee coverage for abortionno matter how much someone earns, how they're insured, or where they live.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: The EACH Act would be a critical step toward ensuring that all people can make decisions about our lives and futures with dignity.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: With abortion access disappearing across the nation, we need the EACH Act now more than ever to ensure reproductive autonomy for all!

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Today marks one full year since Roe v. Wade was overturneda decision that unleashed chaos and uncertainty nationwide.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: We witnessed abortion rights erode as a wave of state bans swept across the US, pushing essential care out of reach for millions of people.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Roe was a cornerstone of reproductive rights, but it didnt ensure equitable access to abortion. Now, access is further limitedespecially for Black, Brown and other people of color and those with the fewest economic resources.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Bodily autonomy is under attack in other ways, too. Since Roe was overturned, anti-abortion state legislators have introduced a slew of bills targeting the health and rights of LGBTQ+ communities, including bans on gender-affirming care for young people.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Our experts have closely monitored these harmful impacts during the past year. In a growing collection of resources, including policy analyses, videos, op-eds, infographics, and more , we've outlined new ways that policymakers, advocates and donors can make a difference in our post-Roe reality.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: As we reflect on whats been lost in the past year, we must also turn our attention to a new vision of equitable abortion access and reproductive autonomy.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: We stand in solidarity with advocates and policymakers who share this vision, and were as committed as ever to making it possible for all.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: As our President and CEO Dr. Herminia Palacio notes, we have seen that the anti-abortion movement will stop at nothing to eliminate access to abortion and other essential health care that all people deserve.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Yet, in the face of these relentless attacks, we know that the fight for reproductive freedom is far from over.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: We stand ready for the work ahead and will never stop fighting to build a future of truly equitable abortion access for all.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: After decades of restrictions and one year since Roe was overturned, the devastating realities of getting abortion care in the US demand new solutions for lasting change.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Introduced today by @repayannapressley, the Abortion Justice Act is bold legislation that would ensure essential health care for anyone who needs it!

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: This is critical as we face an escalating crisis.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Abortion is completely banned in 13 US states and unavailable in Wisconsin. This has left large regions of the country without access to essential care, and increased wait times at clinics in states where abortion remains legal.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Bans hurt everyone, but they're most harmful to people who already face significant barriers to care due to systemic racism and economic injustice. This includes Black, Brown and other people of color, young people, immigrants, LGBTQ+ individuals, and people living with low incomes.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: When these obstacles are layered on top of each other, abortion can be pushed completely out of reach.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: The Abortion Justice Act would address this by protecting the right of all peopleno matter who they are, where they live or how much they maketo get abortion care without unjust barriers or interference. Its a bold step toward ensuring equitable access for all!

The introduction of these bills has only ramped up since Roe was overturned, alongside bans on abortion in many sta...

instances.excerpt: In a new op-ed for @publichealthmag, our experts Kelly Baden and Isabel Guarnieri look at ongoing attacks on abortion access since Roe v. Wade fell one year ago and offer critical steps that policymakers can take to defend abortion access. Some of the most important actions include:

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast

instances.excerpt: Better state policies are crucial, but we need federal protection, too. Congress must pass the Womens Health Protection Act, the Equal Access to Abortion Coverage Act and the HEAL for Immigrant Families Act to restore abortion rights and access nationwide.

instances.excerpt: One year post-Roe, its clear that anti-abortion groups want to control reproductive freedom at all costs. As our experts explain, its time to fight harder than ever before for policies that will ensure health and rights for all.

instances.excerpt: Bans on essential health care: Abortion is now completely banned in 13 states and continues to be unavailable in Wisconsin. This year, we also saw 17 states enact bans on gender-affirming care for young people14 of these states have abortion bans in place.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Attacks on democracy: Anti-abortion state lawmakers have resorted to new tactics to further limit abortion access, including by changing the rules around state ballot measures that have been crucial to expanding abortion rights after the end of Roe.

instances.what: Text outside widget has enhanced contrast
instances.excerpt: Actions to protect abortion: Policymakers in several states worked to expand abortion access in a variety of ways. Importantly, 9 states and DC enacted "shield laws" in 2023 to protect abortion providers and patients from punishments or investigations in states that have banned abortion.

instances.excerpt: Everyone should be able to get essential health care and make decisions about their bodies and lives with dignity. instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: All immigrants deserve access to high-quality health care when they need it. Period.

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: But for many immigrants in the US, getting this care is harder than it should be due to discriminatory policies.

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: The Health Equity and Access under the Law (HEAL) for Immigrant Families Act reintroduced in the House and Senate today aims to tackle this by:

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: Eliminating the 5-year wait for immigrants and migrants with green cards to enroll in Medicaid and Childrens Health Insurance Program (CHIP)

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: Ensuring access to coverage for DACA recipients

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: Enabling immigrants and migrants without documentation to access the ACA Marketplace

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: Our findings from 2019 show that more noncitizen immigrants were uninsured as compared to their US-born and naturalized counterparts. Latino and Black immigrants were most likely to be uninsured.

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: This has serious impacts on noncitizen immigrants access to primary care and sexual and reproductive health care services. Tap the link in bio to learn more

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: Everyone deserves access to health care no matter their race, place of birth, or immigration status. Policymakers must act now to pass the #HEAL4Immigrants Act!

instances.what: Text outside widget has minimum contrast
instances.excerpt: Thank you to @latinainstitute and @napawf for all your work pushing this bill forward!

Some screen readers will announce the capital letters separately (like an acronym) or otherwise misleadingly emphasise the capital letters.

empty_button_description.what: Button has no visible accessible name

texts: The button content has only whitespaces. Having only defined an attribute aria-label="Close dialog" is not sufficient and it is recommended to have the content instead, e.g. at least visually hidden, but exposed to assisitve technologies. Some users are disabling styles for better readability, and also description from attribute is not available for automatic translators.
